# Business Map View

## Overview

The Business Map View provides an interactive map visualization of all business insurance assets, including commercial properties and fleet vehicles. This feature replaces the previous "Coming Soon" placeholder at `/business/map`.

## Technology Stack

- **Mapping Library**: Leaflet via `react-leaflet` v5.0.0
- **Map Tiles**: OpenStreetMap (no API key required)
- **UI Components**: Carbon Design System
- **Styling**: SCSS with theme-aware design tokens

## Component Architecture

### BusinessMapPage (Page Component)

**Location**: `src/pages/business/BusinessMapPage.jsx`

**Purpose**: Page-level wrapper providing layout, filters, and data management

**Key Features**:
- Carbon Grid/Column responsive layout
- Filter toggles to show/hide properties and vehicles
- Legend showing asset types and counts
- Info panel with usage instructions and asset summary
- Navigation to detail pages on marker click

**State Management**:

const [showProperties, setShowProperties] = useState(true);
const [showVehicles, setShowVehicles] = useState(true);
```

**Data Source**: 
- `mockProperties` and `mockVehicles` from `src/data/businessMockData.js`
- Properties: 12 assets with `lat` and `lng` properties
- Vehicles: 30 assets with `lastKnownLocation: { lat, lng }`

**Navigation**:
- Property markers → `/business/properties/:propertyId`
- Vehicle markers → `/business/fleet/:vehicleId`

### BusinessMap (Map Component)

**Location**: `src/components/business/BusinessMap.jsx`

**Purpose**: Self-contained Leaflet map with markers and popups

**Key Features**:
- Leaflet MapContainer with OpenStreetMap tiles
- Custom SVG markers for properties (red) and vehicles (blue)
- Interactive popups with asset details and "View Details" button
- Auto-fit bounds to show all visible markers
- Theme-aware marker and popup styling

**Props**:
```jsx
{
  properties: Array<Property>,      // Properties to display
  vehicles: Array<Vehicle>,          // Vehicles to display
  onMarkerClick: Function,           // Callback: (asset, type) => void
  initialCenter: [lat, lng],         // Default: [37.5, -121.5] (CA)
  initialZoom: Number,               // Default: 7
}
```

**Map Configuration**:
- **Tiles**: `https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png`
- **Attribution**: OpenStreetMap contributors
- **Initial View**: California center (lat: 37.5, lng: -121.5, zoom: 7)
- **Auto-fit**: Bounds automatically adjust to show all markers
- **Controls**: Zoom controls, attribution, scroll wheel zoom enabled

**Custom Markers**:
- Property icon: Red circle with building SVG (uses `--interactive-primary`)
- Vehicle icon: Blue circle with truck SVG (IBM Blue 60/40 for light/dark)
- Icons use `L.divIcon` for full CSS control
- Hover effect: Scale up 1.1x with smooth transition

## Styling Implementation

### Theme-Aware Design Tokens

**Files**:
- `src/pages/business/BusinessMapPage.scss` - Page-level styles
- `src/components/business/BusinessMap.scss` - Map component styles

**Color Tokens Used**:
```scss
--background-primary      // Page and popup backgrounds
--background-secondary    // Map container, stat cards
--text-primary           // Headings, primary text
--text-secondary         // Supporting text, labels
--interactive-primary    // Property markers, brand red
--border-subtle          // Borders, dividers
```

**Dark Mode Adaptations**:
- Map tiles have brightness/contrast filter in dark mode
- Popup backgrounds use `--background-primary` (adapts automatically)
- Vehicle markers use lighter blue (#78a9ff) in dark mode
- All text uses semantic tokens for proper contrast

### Responsive Design

**Breakpoints**:
- **Desktop** (>1056px): Full layout, 600px map height
- **Tablet** (672px-1056px): Stacked controls, 500px map height
- **Mobile** (<672px): Vertical layout, 400px map height

**Mobile Optimizations**:
- Toggle controls stack vertically
- Legend items wrap on small screens
- Info panel grid becomes single column
- Font sizes reduce slightly

