## User Interactions

### Filter Controls

**Properties Toggle**:
- Label: "Show Properties"
- Default: ON
- Action: Shows/hides all 12 property markers

**Vehicles Toggle**:
- Label: "Show Vehicles"
- Default: ON
- Action: Shows/hides all 30 vehicle markers

**Behavior**:
- When both OFF: Displays "No assets to display" message
- Asset count updates dynamically: "Showing X of Y assets"

### Marker Interactions

**Click Marker**:
1. Popup opens with asset details
2. "View Details" button navigates to detail page
3. Popup has close button (X) in top-right

**Popup Content - Properties**:
- Name (e.g., "Downtown Office Building")
- Address
- Property type
- Status badge (color-coded)
- "View Details" button

**Popup Content - Vehicles**:
- Make/model/year (e.g., "2022 Ford Transit")
- License plate
- Assigned driver
- Vehicle type
- Status badge (color-coded)
- "View Details" button

### Map Controls

- **Zoom**: +/- buttons (top-left)
- **Pan**: Click and drag
- **Scroll Wheel Zoom**: Enabled by default
- **Attribution**: Bottom-right corner

## Status Badges

**Colors** (theme-aware):
- `Active`: Green background, success color
- `In Repair`: Yellow background, warning color
- `Pending Renewal`: Blue background, info color
- `Inactive`: Gray background, tertiary text

## Accessibility Features

### Keyboard Navigation
- Tab through toggles and map controls
- Enter/Space to activate toggles
- Escape to close popups

### Screen Reader Support
- Toggle labels are descriptive
- Map has `aria-label` or descriptive label
- Popups announce asset details
- Buttons have clear labels

### Visual Accessibility
- WCAG AA contrast ratios maintained in both themes
- Focus indicators visible on all interactive elements
- High contrast mode support (increased border widths)
- Marker icons have drop shadows for visibility

### Motion
- Reduced motion support: Transitions disabled
- Animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Performance Considerations

### Current Load
- 12 properties + 30 vehicles = 42 markers total
- Performance is excellent with this count
- No clustering currently needed

### Future Enhancements (If Needed)
- Marker clustering for 100+ markers (use `react-leaflet-cluster`)
- Virtualization for large datasets
- Lazy loading of marker data

